item.title: How do i make client low memory version?
item.dc:creator: @Java_Is_My_Bitch Java Is My Bitch™
item.description:
@Java_Is_My_Bitch wrote:

Tico135:

Yes it does. The MoparScape Client is considered a low-memory version client, and other ‘user made’ clients are classified as high-memory clients. Why would you want it to make your client low-memory? Wouldn’t high-memory be better. The difference is that low memory uses less PC usage (RAM) and is not able to play music. As with the high memory client is opposite.

Also it won’t you use own computers ram. It uses the person with the high memory clients ram. Doesn’t matter which one they use. depending on your ram, the versions vary. In which would be better for you that is.
